Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art showing pecked, infilled figures of three Nile river boats. Leftmost is clearest, with 10 oars and ostrich-like figure with extra protuberance at neck above, upright and facing left. Above this is another with oars pointing up, to right another, similar, cut off edge of image at right. Below and above this boat are two unidentified shapes also cut off. El-Kanais, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
